# Fix: Preview Drawer Shows No Detection Data After CSV Upload

## Root Cause Analysis

The preview drawer on the DataUpload page shows no detection data because **the detection pipeline never sees the uploaded CSV data**. Here's the exact chain of failure:

### The Broken Data Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["CSV Upload (final-boss-audit.csv)"] --> B["csvIngestionService detects as 'inventory' type"]
    B --> C["Data inserted into 'inventory_items' table"]
    C --> D["enhancedDetectionService.triggerDetectionPipeline()"]
    D --> E["Whale Hunter calls fetchInventoryLedger()"]
    E --> F["fetchInventoryLedger reads from: shipments, returns, orders, settlements"]
    F --> G["❌ inventory_items is NEVER queried → 0 events found"]
    G --> H["0 detections → nothing stored in detection_results"]
    H --> I["Frontend preview drawer fetches detection_results → empty"]
```

### Bug 1: `inventory_items` table is never read by detection algorithms

- [csvIngestionService.ts](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/src/services/csvIngestionService.ts#L622-L658) — [ingestInventory()](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/src/services/csvIngestionService.ts#622-659) inserts CSV data into `inventory_items` table
- [inventoryAlgorithms.ts](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/src/services/detection/algorithms/inventoryAlgorithms.ts#L396-L567) — [fetchInventoryLedger()](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/src/services/detection/algorithms/inventoryAlgorithms.ts#390-568) reads from `shipments`, `returns`, `orders`, `settlements` but **never** from `inventory_items`

The [final-boss-audit.csv](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/final-boss-audit.csv) has headers `Date,FNSKU,ASIN,MSKU,Title,Event Type,...` which matches the `inventory` type signature. So data goes into `inventory_items`, but the Whale Hunter algorithm builds its ledger from the *other* tables it never touches.

### Bug 2: Missing `tenant_id` in algorithm-level storage

- [inventoryAlgorithms.ts storeDetectionResults()](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/src/services/detection/algorithms/inventoryAlgorithms.ts#L607-L651) inserts into `detection_results` **without** `tenant_id`
- [detectionService.ts getDetectionResults()](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/src/services/detectionService.ts#L1690-L1746) filters by `tenant_id` (line 1718) when provided, so even if results existed, they'd be invisible to the frontend

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Bug 1 is the primary cause — no detections are ever generated from inventory CSV data. Bug 2 is a secondary issue that would still cause data to be invisible even if Bug 1 were fixed.

