## Proposed Changes

### Component 1: Inventory Detection Algorithm

#### [MODIFY] [inventoryAlgorithms.ts](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/src/services/detection/algorithms/inventoryAlgorithms.ts)

**Fix [fetchInventoryLedger()](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/src/services/detection/algorithms/inventoryAlgorithms.ts#390-568) to also read from `inventory_items` table:**

Add a new query section (after the existing settlements query, before the sort) that reads from `inventory_items` and converts the rows into [InventoryLedgerEvent](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/src/services/detection/algorithms/inventoryAlgorithms.ts#33-51) objects. The `inventory_items` table has fields like `fnsku`, `asin`, [sku](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/src/services/detection/algorithms/inventoryAlgorithms.ts#140-156), `quantity_available`, `dimensions.damaged`, etc. that need to be mapped to `Snapshot` events (for warehouse balances) and any event_type-like fields from the CSV's `Event Type` column (stored in the raw data or mapped during ingestion).

The key mapping:
- `inventory_items` rows with quantity data → `Snapshot` events (providing `warehouse_balance`)
- This gives the Whale Hunter the `endingWarehouseBalance` it needs to detect discrepancies

**Fix [storeDetectionResults()](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/src/services/detection/algorithms/inventoryAlgorithms.ts#604-652) to include `tenant_id`:**

Look up the user's `tenant_id` from the `users` table (same pattern used in [detectionService.ts](file:///c:/Users/Student/Contacts/Clario-Complete-Backend/Integrations-backend/src/services/detectionService.ts) line 1586-1598) and include it in the insert. Add a fallback for sandbox/dev mode.

